491
00:27:02.460 --> 00:27:04.940
And we get bent out of shape,

492
00:27:04.940 --> 00:27:06.420
especially if something's off

493
00:27:07.460 --> 00:27:10.980
and that same desire to have everything right

494
00:27:10.980 --> 00:27:14.540
in appearances can transfer into church life as well.

495
00:27:14.540 --> 00:27:17.420
We can get fixated on wanting, I don't know,

496
00:27:17.420 --> 00:27:21.620
numbers to be big or programs to be spectacular.

497
00:27:21.620 --> 00:27:22.460
Well, the good news is

498
00:27:22.460 --> 00:27:24.540
we don't have to worry about that right now.

499
00:27:24.540 --> 00:27:26.500
So that's good.

500
00:27:27.380 --> 00:27:32.380
But we can still want to appear to each other.

501
00:27:32.460 --> 00:27:35.260
We all have it together, like everything's okay.

502
00:27:35.260 --> 00:27:37.260
The packaging is just right.

503
00:27:38.260 --> 00:27:41.140
The thing is Jesus doesn't turn up

504
00:27:41.140 --> 00:27:43.300
once we get everything together.

505
00:27:43.300 --> 00:27:46.820
He meets us right in the middle of our mess.

506
00:27:46.820 --> 00:27:48.280
He already sees the things

507
00:27:48.280 --> 00:27:51.580
that we would rather keep hidden away

508
00:27:51.580 --> 00:27:53.580
unless knowing him is far better

509
00:27:53.580 --> 00:27:56.780
than pretending like we have it all together.

510
00:27:56.780 --> 00:27:59.700
We're gonna know his presence and work among us.

511
00:27:59.700 --> 00:28:02.300
It's gonna come with owning our own unimpressiveness

512
00:28:02.300 --> 00:28:06.540
that we might see his glorious saving,

513
00:28:06.540 --> 00:28:10.580
life changing work in our midst together.

514
00:28:10.580 --> 00:28:14.500
I love how Sam Albury changed the opening line

515
00:28:14.500 --> 00:28:16.580
of, oh, come all you faithful,

516
00:28:16.580 --> 00:28:18.900
perhaps to reflect this a bit more faithfully.

517
00:28:18.900 --> 00:28:21.580
He said this, he said, oh, come all you faithless,

518
00:28:21.580 --> 00:28:23.660
joyless and defeated.

519
00:28:23.660 --> 00:28:26.700
Christmas is for the weary, for the messed up

520
00:28:26.700 --> 00:28:28.220
and for the broken.

521
00:28:28.220 --> 00:28:30.580
If your life isn't Instagrammable,

522
00:28:30.580 --> 00:28:32.380
Christmas is for you.

523
00:28:33.220 --> 00:28:38.020
So we come to a Christ who's ready to receive us.

524
00:28:41.020 --> 00:28:42.980
We just sang earlier, a little town of Bethlehem.

525
00:28:42.980 --> 00:28:45.400
It says we're Meek souls, not the proud souls,

526
00:28:45.400 --> 00:28:46.360
not the impressive souls.

527
00:28:46.360 --> 00:28:48.380
We're Meek souls will receive him

528
00:28:48.380 --> 00:28:51.340
still the dear Christ enters in.

529
00:28:52.460 --> 00:28:55.320
He plans himself like a root in dry ground.

530
00:28:57.500 --> 00:29:00.060
So own our unimpressiveness,

531
00:29:00.060 --> 00:29:01.920
but also believe the gospel.

532
00:29:01.920 --> 00:29:03.440
That's the second way we should respond.

533
00:29:03.440 --> 00:29:06.440
Believe the good news of Jesus.

534
00:29:06.440 --> 00:29:08.440
The gospel, the good news of Jesus' death

535
00:29:08.440 --> 00:29:10.440
and resurrection is the power of God

536
00:29:10.440 --> 00:29:14.000
and the salvation for everyone who believes.

537
00:29:14.000 --> 00:29:15.520
So scripture is given to us.

538
00:29:16.880 --> 00:29:19.060
The book of Isaiah is given to us

539
00:29:19.060 --> 00:29:22.640
that we might look beyond what our physical eyes

540
00:29:22.640 --> 00:29:27.280
can see and see the work of God by faith.

541
00:29:27.280 --> 00:29:31.860
We can see that no, the situation might look hopeless,

542
00:29:31.860 --> 00:29:33.880
but through the eyes of faith, believing the gospel,

543
00:29:33.880 --> 00:29:36.340
we can say, no, actually God is present

544
00:29:36.340 --> 00:29:38.700
and he is at work whether I see it or not

545
00:29:38.700 --> 00:29:41.540
and I can know that he will bring to completion

546
00:29:41.540 --> 00:29:43.620
what he began.

547
00:29:43.620 --> 00:29:48.300
I can believe the message of the gospel.

548
00:29:48.300 --> 00:29:50.820
This changes how we see Jesus.

549
00:29:50.820 --> 00:29:54.700
People, when we look through the eyes of faith,

550
00:29:54.700 --> 00:29:57.100
people might ignore historical evidence

551
00:29:57.100 --> 00:29:58.900
or brush him off as just a legend

552
00:29:58.900 --> 00:30:02.380
or as an antiquated belief in the past.

553
00:30:03.620 --> 00:30:07.220
By faith, we see him as the savior and king.

554
00:30:07.220 --> 00:30:09.180
And it changes how we see our circumstances

555
00:30:09.180 --> 00:30:11.580
when we look at them through the eyes of faith.

556
00:30:15.580 --> 00:30:19.060
By faith, we see that our lives,

557
00:30:19.060 --> 00:30:22.060
including the things we struggle with,

558
00:30:22.060 --> 00:30:24.620
are just the sort of place where Christ plants himself

559
00:30:25.060 --> 00:30:28.860
and where his glory is made known.

560
00:30:30.300 --> 00:30:32.820
His power is made perfect in our weakness.

561
00:30:33.960 --> 00:30:38.960
But not only that, so we own our own unimpressiveness,

562
00:30:39.260 --> 00:30:40.860
but in that we believe the gospel

563
00:30:40.860 --> 00:30:43.220
that Christ plants himself in our lives

564
00:30:43.220 --> 00:30:45.540
and gives us his life.

565
00:30:45.540 --> 00:30:46.900
And then when we believe the gospel

566
00:30:46.900 --> 00:30:48.500
and we believe that God is at work

567
00:30:48.500 --> 00:30:51.080
and he will bring to completion what he began,

568
00:30:51.080 --> 00:30:56.080
we can then sing for joy, which we're gonna do here in a second.

569
00:30:56.440 --> 00:30:58.440
On this third Sunday of Advent,

570
00:30:58.440 --> 00:31:00.200
we began by thinking about joy.

571
00:31:00.200 --> 00:31:01.680
That candle's still going, great.

572
00:31:04.640 --> 00:31:05.880
But we see this here.

573
00:31:05.880 --> 00:31:07.600
In Isaiah 52 and verse eight,

574
00:31:07.600 --> 00:31:09.920
we see that the result of God's saving work

575
00:31:09.920 --> 00:31:13.660
in the midst of his people is that they sing for joy.

576
00:31:15.200 --> 00:31:17.960
Isaiah 53 is a very well-known chapter

577
00:31:17.960 --> 00:31:18.920
in the Old Testament,

578
00:31:18.920 --> 00:31:22.240
but perhaps not as well-known as how the next chapter starts.

579
00:31:22.240 --> 00:31:24.600
After having seen Christ crucify,

580
00:31:24.600 --> 00:31:28.640
Isaiah 54 begins with this word, sing.

581
00:31:28.640 --> 00:31:32.500
That's how we respond to seeing Christ for who he truly is.

582
00:31:33.440 --> 00:31:35.880
When Jesus instituted the Lord's supper

583
00:31:38.400 --> 00:31:41.600
and right before he went to Gethsemane and the cross,

584
00:31:41.600 --> 00:31:43.320
sometimes we can skip over the bit

585
00:31:43.320 --> 00:31:44.400
that happens in the middle of that.

586
00:31:44.400 --> 00:31:45.800
When they finished the supper,

587
00:31:45.800 --> 00:31:47.920
he spoke about his body being broken,

588
00:31:47.920 --> 00:31:49.600
his blood being poured out.

589
00:31:49.600 --> 00:31:52.080
He knew what was about to befall him.

590
00:31:52.080 --> 00:31:53.840
And yet before he went out,

591
00:31:53.840 --> 00:31:55.920
what did he do with his disciples?

592
00:31:55.920 --> 00:31:56.760
He sang with them.

593
00:31:56.760 --> 00:31:59.000
It says they sang at him together.

594
00:31:59.000 --> 00:32:03.920
And it was traditional to sing Psalm 114 to Psalm 118.

595
00:32:03.920 --> 00:32:06.480
We don't know exactly if they sang all the verses of that

596
00:32:06.480 --> 00:32:07.320
or if that's what they sang.

597
00:32:07.320 --> 00:32:08.560
But at the time of Passover,

598
00:32:08.560 --> 00:32:11.320
that's what the Lord's people sang.

599
00:32:11.320 --> 00:32:13.120
So no doubt they sang that.

600
00:32:13.960 --> 00:32:15.640
It's looking through Psalm 118

601
00:32:15.880 --> 00:32:19.560
and it's a Psalm that says these words,

602
00:32:19.560 --> 00:32:22.000
this is the day the Lord has made.

603
00:32:22.000 --> 00:32:26.080
We will rejoice and be glad in it.

604
00:32:26.080 --> 00:32:27.480
So whatever we are facing,

605
00:32:27.480 --> 00:32:28.800
we can look to Christ

606
00:32:30.120 --> 00:32:32.360
and all that we've been promised in him

607
00:32:32.360 --> 00:32:36.920
and we can defiantly sing for joy.

608
00:32:36.920 --> 00:32:37.760
Let's pray.

609
00:32:42.240 --> 00:32:44.040
Lord, thank you so much

610
00:32:44.080 --> 00:32:48.160
for your word and what you've spoken us about,

611
00:32:48.160 --> 00:32:51.440
how you've pointed us to Jesus.

612
00:32:51.440 --> 00:32:55.480
Lord, we thank you for how he humbled himself

613
00:32:55.480 --> 00:32:58.720
and became a man and even humbled himself

614
00:32:58.720 --> 00:33:01.240
to the point of death on a cross.

615
00:33:03.280 --> 00:33:05.360
Lord, he was despised and rejected.

616
00:33:06.480 --> 00:33:08.400
Lord, we thank you that he did that for us.

617
00:33:08.400 --> 00:33:10.520
Lord, that he took our,

618
00:33:10.520 --> 00:33:15.520
not only our humanity and our suffering,

619
00:33:15.840 --> 00:33:17.600
but also he took on our sin

620
00:33:17.600 --> 00:33:19.600
and died in our place on the cross.

621
00:33:21.080 --> 00:33:23.600
Lord, we thank you for his triumphant resurrection

622
00:33:24.720 --> 00:33:28.200
and Lord that he reigns forevermore.

623
00:33:28.200 --> 00:33:29.800
Lord, we thank you for everything

624
00:33:29.800 --> 00:33:32.600
that was accomplished through his death and resurrection.

625
00:33:33.720 --> 00:33:34.880
Lord, we can know that one day

626
00:33:34.880 --> 00:33:38.060
we will be with you forever through faith in him.

627
00:33:39.060 --> 00:33:43.180
So Lord, I pray that whatever we are looking at today

628
00:33:43.180 --> 00:33:44.660
and in the weeks ahead,

629
00:33:44.660 --> 00:33:49.660
whether it appears to us to be wonderful and impressive

630
00:33:50.860 --> 00:33:53.180
or small and insignificant,

631
00:33:53.180 --> 00:33:55.220
Lord, I pray that we would not ultimately be looking

632
00:33:55.220 --> 00:33:58.140
to those things for our hope, for our joy,

633
00:33:58.140 --> 00:34:00.700
rather we would be looking to Jesus.

634
00:34:01.540 --> 00:34:05.660
Lord, I pray that Christ would plant himself among us.

635
00:34:05.660 --> 00:34:08.020
We would know his life in our midst

636
00:34:08.020 --> 00:34:10.340
and we would rejoice in him.

637
00:34:10.340 --> 00:34:13.380
Help us to do that even now we pray in Jesus' name.

